{"type":"message","id":"80560010","parentId":"e6e6bbfc","timestamp":"2026-05-20T20:09:19.651Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The issue now is with U+3002 (。) the ideographic full stop character. In Python 3.14, this character is being flagged as invalid due to confusables/security policy. Let me check what other characters might be problematic.\n\nActually, looking more carefully at the error: `invalid character '。' (U+3002)` - the ideographic period `。` is being flagged. This is a known Python 3.12+ behavior where certain characters in strings/comments can be flagged.\n\nWait, but Python typically allows these characters in string literals. The issue might be that this is a docstring and the character is being flagged. Let me check if this is a confusables issue.\n\n\nLet me re-examine the actual error message more carefully - the console rendering is garbled, but it seems like the arrow character and ideographic period are both being flagged. The U+2192 (→) has been replaced with ASCII `->`, so that shouldn't be the problem anymore. Let me look at the exact bytes in the file to see what's actually there.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"The `。` (U+3002) ideographic full stop is also being flagged by Python 3.14. Let me replace all problematic characters:\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_f5ae91f8866e40aeb49ff3f7","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python -c \"\npath = r'D:\\astro_py\\astro_hub\\src\\main\\main.py'\nwith open(path, 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f:\n    text = f.read()\n\n# Check for all non-ASCII characters that might be problematic\nproblematic = []\nfor i, ch in enumerate(text):\n    code = ord(ch)\n    if code > 127:\n        # Check if it's a known problematic character in Python 3.12+\n        # Characters like U+2192, U+3002 etc. can be flagged\n        line = text[:i].count('\\n') + 1\n        problematic.append((i, code, hex(code), ch, line))\n\nprint('Non-ASCII characters found: %d' % len(problematic))\nprint()\n# Group by character\nfrom collections import Counter\nchar_counts = Counter((code, ch) for _, code, _, ch, _ in problematic)\nfor (code, ch), count in sorted(char_counts.items(), key=lambda x: x[0][0]):\n    print('  U+%04X (%s): %d occurrences' % (code, ch, count))\n\""}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"YerPlan","model":"qwen3.6-plus","usage":{"input":51081,"output":564,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":51645,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779307745694,"responseId":"msg_78a478c8-1550-4a26-b7d0-62ed19419f8b"}}
